Yesterday was nice. No school cause of the snow. Today, we only have a 2-hour delay. Drab. I know how to play "Smells Like Teen Spirit" on the guitar now! I've had only one thought running through my brain lately. It's pumping through my veins like adrenaline. 

Gotta be a rockstar. Gotta be a rockstar. Gotta be a rockstar. 

Poetic Dark Angel came by last night (oooh codenames. they shouldn't be hard to crack if you know me). We almost made love in the snow after a night filled with brownies (only partially burnt!!!) and videogames that I suck at. This is the life and times of a Rockstar. Get to know me now 'cause I'll be famous one day.

7 entries found for love.
love    ( P )  Pronunciation Key  (lv)
n. 
A deep, tender, ineffable feeling of affection and solicitude toward a person, such as that arising from kinship, recognition of attractive qualities, or a sense of underlying oneness. 
A feeling of intense desire and attraction toward a person with whom one is disposed to make a pair; the emotion of sex and romance. 

Sexual passion. 
Sexual intercourse. 
A love affair. 
An intense emotional attachment, as for a pet or treasured object. 
A person who is the object of deep or intense affection or attraction; beloved. Often used as a term of endearment. 
An expression of one's affection: Send him my love. 

A strong predilection or enthusiasm: a love of language. 
The object of such an enthusiasm: The outdoors is her greatest love. 
Love Mythology. Eros or Cupid. 
often Love Christianity. Charity. 
Sports. A zero score in tennis.

Here's a new part to my Magnolia story: "I don't want to die." I thought as I drove towards Jamal's apartment. How can I live with my heart half beating? Tears are hiding behind my eyes trying to escape and rain is pouring from the sky. If God can cry, why can't I? I'm now in front of his door and I'm soaked. The cold in my bones echoes the icy chill in my heart. My cold fist knocks on the door but I'm not there. I'm outside of myself trying to tell my body to Run Away. Save yourself. Save myself. Love Hurts, Love Scars. Remember? No one answers the door and I try to tell myself to leave. Go home and cry with no tears. Dry my dry eyes and live a normal life. A life free of this painful obsession with love. Instead of leaving I'm unlocking the door. For the first time in my life I'm ready to apologize. Ready to beg for forgiveness. I open the door and all my apologies fall to the floor, unspoken. She's kissing him. She's kissing my angel. And he's holding her the way he used to hold me. The way he still holds me in my dreams. He's kissing her the way he kissed me and I wish I was her. Trapped in the doorway like a deer caught in headlights. Eyes wet and wide, waiting for impact. The rain is at my back and the pain is in my eyes. The heat between me and Amber's body is interrupted by a cold wind brushing my skin. She sees her before I do, but I feel her presence before anything else. My heart breaks because hers is shattered. But Amber is still in my arms. My fingers are going pale from gripping the doorknob too hard. I want to leap forward like a beautiful animal, maybe a lion or a tiger, and tear her limb from limb. I want to cut her 'til she bleeds. I want her to hurt like I am hurting. I want to break her into pieces. She's standing in the doorway, but Amber and I are still standing here, half holding each other. How long have we stood her? Still as statues. The cinema in Magnolia's eyes has closed the curtain. The pain in her eyes killed me, but the emptiness that replaced it is destroying me. The fire in her eyes has died and I think my soul died with it.

I'm afraid of being tickled to death, and dying in a METROrail subway station. Seriously. I've always wondered about wether it's possible to ACTUALLY be tickled to death. My friend Rachel teases me about and tickles me until my stomach feels like its about to explode. Just to freak me out. I'm also afraid of dying in a METRO station. I hate it when Charles walks really close to the tracks. I hate it when anyone walks to close to the tracks. I can't run and play in the train statio because I'm scared of falling in the tracks. I'm also afraid of getting stuck in the train doors. I also have the same fear with elevators. I've gotten stuck in elevator doors before. Not fun. I always wonder what would happen if the doors don't open and the elevator starts to go up. Or down. When I was small, I was afraid of escalaters. It used to get on my stepmothers (may God bless her soul during her stay in Heaven) nerves. It would take forever to persuade me to step onto the moving steps. 'Tis the life of a coward. Oh Well. Atleast my room is clean. (That's my answer to everything!)
Doesn't it look so pretty. It's not finished yet though. I might change the background.

Why isn't Charles here yet? Thanks to my mother I completely wasted a whole Saturday! Ugh. School starts Monday. Well, atleast my room is clean.
If I had my way I would've been out of the house since 10:00. I would've been skateboarding in Chinatown with my honey angel. But nooo I have to be in the house wasting my life away. And it's to late for me to go anywher now because my curfew is freaking 6:30. Nine year olds have later curfews than me. I have about a year and a half until I graduate. Then I will be free.

My friends find it funny how excited I get about Christmas. But how can one not get excited. I probably act this way because I've only celebrated Christmas about five times in my life. That's what I get for having a Mother who's Muslim and a Dad who's a Jehovah's Witness. Charles got me a present and he won't tell me what it is!

Woo Hoo! Rachel let me borrow her Nirvana CD! Happiness. I had a sleepover with an 8 year old this weekend. 8 year olds are fun. I feel like such a kid. It was me, Rachel, and Teyarn (the 8 year old). We made pasta, pudding, jello, burnt popcorn and pancakes. The jello was gelatin free! No nasty animal hooves for me. My mom bought it from the Islamic Market (aka The Halal Market). It was Mango flavored and yummy. We played video games and went to the craft store. I had so much fun this weekend. Little Kids are cool.
Ha ha. My big brother is such a kid. Watching Saturday morning cartoons and playing video games. I love him sooooo much!

The air in the oversized manson crackled with electric energy. It smelled like the sweat of rockstars and pixies. Salty and Sweet. Nick and Flint had outdone themselves. In the main ballroom people dressed as faeries, wolves, vamps, angels and lanka witches (or were they faeries, wolves, vamps, angels and lanka witches dressed as people) danced, talked and gyrated to the beat of the techno-hiphop-rock-soul music that blasted from invisible speakers. Neon lights, glowsticks, glitter, and bubbles floated around the crowded room. Servers in sarongs, kimonos, togas, and headresses carried plates of sushi, falafals, hummus, baklava, and other assorted dishes and desserts. Tables overflowed with even more food. A party was in full swing in every one of what seemed to be a limitless number of rooms.

I've been spending to much time on this computer lately. Between all my FBLA work (i'm president), working on my Business Plan for Entrepreneurship, class projects, and other random work I'm so busy. Also trying to have some kind of social life. And I'm scared my creativity may be waning. 
All work and no play makes this girl a dull goddess.
Write now I'm working on my business plan so that it will be ready for my class competition on the 16th. I know I'm gonna win. Atleast I can listen to good music when I'm on the computer. All I hear on the radio is rap, r&b, and top 20 countdowns. Yawn. I also have Leaders of Tomorrow to go to today. After that I'm just gonna relax. I'll probably go to Rachels house and rock out on the guitar with her.

This is from my real diary that I carry with me always. The quotes are from Missing Angel Juan by Francesca Lia Block. "Some Native Americans believe that the drum is the heart of the universe. What happens to the rest of something when you smash it's heart?" What happens?!? "My throat hurts like my voice is made of broken glass" "Angel Juan ha taken my mind and my heart away and his ghost is trapped in the empty places that are left..." I think maybe being with Charles (the love of my life, soulmate, secret agent, jah love, angel) has caused a different sadness. A sadness that's more of a void than an emotion. The void created when he's not by my side. The absence of love. Like darkness is the absence of light. Like cold is the absence of heat. My grief is the absence of Charles. "...not so I feel like he's always with me. Just like always remembering that he's not."

Remember in Elementary school when we made those paper mache dinosaur eggs? They were a colorful tissue paper exterior with a few pieces of candy rattling around on the inside. That's how I feel now. The subway train is pushing me around as my heart ratles against my hollow chest. My soul feels empty. And my heart is harder than last years halloween candy.

Pumpkin Custard Pie is delicious until you get addicted and eat too much. I also have a cold. Blech. I realize that nobody reads this journal. I also realize that I don't type in this journal. That's probably gonna change now.
